		"Name": "Super-Cooled Myomer (S)",
		"Details": "The Sanctuary Worlds pursued a very different technological path than the Inner Sphere or the Clans. In their endless experimentation and development, they came across a way to integrate heat sinking technology into a BattleMech's myomer systems. This invention came to be known as Super-Cooled Myomer (SCM) and was put into limited use by the Dane Sacellum to help maintain the heating levels on several of their more heat-intensive BattleMech designs. While SCM is very effective at cooling a 'Mech's weapons systems, it is also quite bulky, taking a good amount of internal space to operate, making it somewhat more of a niche option for engineers.",
